em capable of producing and sustaining debates in which imperiled species serve as proxies for broader conflicts about the politics of place. The challenge for conservationists in the twenty-first century, this book claims, will be to redefine habitat conservation beyond protected wildlands to build more diverse and sustainable landscapes.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEndangered specieszCalifornia. 0aEndangered specieszUnited States. 0aGrizzly bearzCalifornia. 0aWildlife conservationzCalifornia. 0aWildlife conservationzUnited States. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh  a21st century habitat conservation.  aamerican culture.  aamerican politics.  aamerican wildlife.  aaspca.  abooks for nature lovers.  acalifornia gold rush.  acalifornia history.  acalifornia wildlife.  acondor.  aconservation of wildlife.  adesert tortoise.  aeasy to read.  aendangered species.  aengaging.  aenvironmental conservation protection.  aenvironmental ecology.  ago green.  ahow to protect animals.  ainteresting books.  anonfiction books.  apolitics and science.  apreserving wildlife.  asaving the environment.  ascience and math.  asustaining landscapes.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052027506540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095441040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520954410423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520954410/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY